Use Jobs to Get Predictions

In Einstein Studio, a prediction job enables an active model to write inferences, which you can append to a data model object (DMO). Create a streaming or batch job without leaving Einstein Studio, and consume the predicted outputs in Salesforce workflows.

To find a model in Einstein Studio, click the model, and then select Model Details.
Select your model. Then click New Prediction Job.
Select the data space and DMO. Then click Next.
Map the model schema fields to your input fields. Then click Next.
NOTE The inputs defined here initiate updates to your prediction when data on these fields change. To activate a prediction job, you must also map all fields.
To add a DMO for your inputs, click the object field and select Add an object.
On Available Objects, select the object and all its associated direct attributes.
To add related attributes, select a default path to begin mapping your fields. Then click Select {"default path name"}.
On Added Objects, review all your added objects.
To remove an added object, click Remove.
To see your mapped fields, click Back to Mapping.
To choose the job update type, select streaming or batch. Then click Next.
NOTE Streaming predictions automatically update when your input data changes and keeps your predictions up to date. To update batch predictions, you must manually refresh.
Define which fields initiate updates to your prediction, and then click Next.
Review your prediction job settings.
If you must make changes, update your settings. Then click Next.
Add a job name and description, and then click Create.
After the job is created, you can find it in Model Details.
NOTE

A new DMO is created to store predictions for streaming jobs.
